    "Description": "\"Ooinaru Umi e (To the Great Sea)\" served as the opening theme for the 1979-80 Sci-Fi anime \"Space Carrier Blue Noah\" (also known as \"Thundersub\"). Composed by Masaaki Hirai - whose work also shaped the iconic sound of Galaxy Express 999 - the original track was oddly handed to an idol singer, resulting in a performance that never quite matched the song's potential.\nFor this version, I set out to revive its brilliance with a soaring female vocal and a bold new arrangement. There are a few spots where the delivery didn't land exactly as intended, but overall I think the piece has gained a powerful new life.\nPlease enjoy this revitalized tribute to a classic theme!",
